explanation: A style sheet language used for specifying the presentation and styling of a document written in a markup language such as HTML or XML.
Text file that has a specific format which allows data to be saved in a table structured format.
Language and file format for storing, transmitting, and reconstructing arbitrary data.
Standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser. It defines the content and structure of web content.
Unique identifier used to locate a resource on the Internet. It is also referred to as a web address.
